README


pml:
-------
You can view the annotated treebank pml files with the tree editor TrEd, download from:

https://ufal.mff.cuni.cz/tred/

qu_schema.xml is the schema file.

tred_macros contains an extension to TrEd with some additional functions to view the Quechua trees.
Copy the folder quechua in tred_macros to YOUR_HOME/.tred.d/extensions and add 'quechua' to the file YOUR_HOME/.tred.d/extensions/extensions.lst

conll:
--------
contains the treebanks in conll format


scripts:  
---------
quzconll2pml.pl  converts conll to pml
pml2conll.pml    converts pml to conll


DZ: Convert PML to CoNLL-U using Treex:

cd ahk1968-2008/
treex -Lquz Read::QuechuaPML from="ahk1968-2008_qu.pml" Write::CoNLLU print_zone_id=0 to="ahk1968-2008_qu.conllu"

(It may not work if invoked from a different folder because the PML file contains a relative reference to the PML schema.)

